TopicTitle: [1.0.5] RSS Planets & Moons expanded v0.12.0 Sedna is finally here!

Articles.Content:
10 minutes ago, pozine said:

In RSS, making it to LEO is hard. Making it to another nearby planet is very hard. And making it to Sedna would be Chuck Norris hard. We humans are masochists.

Sorry, Sedna is just so far off and mysterious, you have to add that. Also, it might be hard getting the correct amounts of Dv to get there, but its orbital period is so long (11400 earth years) that it should look as if it just hangs on one spot.

It is quite dissapointing that it is currently at it's perihelion, though. It will be even more mysterious, cold, dark and challenging if it will be at its aphelion. But hey, we'll all die long before we see that.

Edited December 19, 2015 by 073198681

"Once your in orbit your halfway to anywhere" - Robert Heinlein.

Edited December 19, 2015 by Motokid600
Sedna is officialy done. It will be in next version and it is far...REALLY REALLY far from the sun.

First off all: Thanks for this great expansion pack!

 

I use the LITE-Version off the expansion pack and I am missing Titania, the biggist moon of Uranus. I can see that the LITE-Version includes Titania but it isn't loaded.

 

Can someone help me? Does someone have the same problem?

9 hours ago, Soli said:

First off all: Thanks for this great expansion pack!

 

I use the LITE-Version off the expansion pack and I am missing Titania, the biggist moon of Uranus. I can see that the LITE-Version includes Titania but it isn't loaded.

 

Can someone help me? Does someone have the same problem?

I had a look at files from both versions, and they're exactly the same. I don't know what happened.

1- Delete your cache (Kopernicus/cache folder, delete everything inside)

2-Start KSP and look for Titania

 

If it doesn't work, delete the cache again and try replacing Titania related files from LITE version by those in the normal version?

Edited December 31, 2015 by pozine
I have deleted the cache again and replaced Titania related files, but still no Titania.
Then, it is my error. Thank you, i'll solve this.

I don't know why, but my contacts which involves the Moon, and all my satellites put on there were transferred to Vesta, and my Mars contracts/satellites were transfered to the Moon Oo after I installed this mod. LOL.
There is something that  I can do to solve that?

Thanks, in advance. Awesome mod! Please, keep doing!

Another question

For anyone wondering, I've sent a lander to Sedna once in my own custom mod, last year. I used an enormous electric propulsion ship. It was a one way journey with the kerbals trapped in their tiny lander. Quite the place.

 

Point is, it's possible, you should add it because this is currently an awesome mod.

Where does it hang?

8 hours ago, kimjongspoon said:

It loads all of the textures and the little yellow loading bar is full, but it never loads the start screen.

How long have you waited? First time you start ksp after installing this mod Kopernicus needs to rebuild scaled space meshes, which can take quite a while. I suggest you leave it running for 15 mins or so.

hi everyone!! first of all I would like to say what a great great great mod @pozine !!!! a fantastic addition to RSS, it makes the whole experience way richer and entertaining!

I tried to incorporate this mod to my current 1.0.4 career save - I installed & loaded up the mod without any problems, the only issue being that all of my vessels on and around the Moon are now located on Vesta - is there any way to work around this??? 

many thanks for this great addition to the game!!!

13 hours ago, pvnkb1tch said:

hi everyone!! first of all I would like to say what a great great great mod @pozine !!!! a fantastic addition to RSS, it makes the whole experience way richer and entertaining!

I tried to incorporate this mod to my current 1.0.4 career save - I installed & loaded up the mod without any problems, the only issue being that all of my vessels on and around the Moon are now located on Vesta - is there any way to work around this??? 

many thanks for this great addition to the game!!!

I had the same thing happen. Just go into your save file and under the REF = X section of a specific vessel, change it from 10 to 11 if around the moon and 11 to 12 if around Mars.

Small update today.

- Added Sedna

- Solved Titania from not appearing ingame

- Updated to Kopernicus 0.6.3
Any chance of adding the asteroid Eros in the future? And maybe Planet Nine?

On 30/1/2016 at 5:14 PM, Mitchz95 said:

Any chance of adding the asteroid Eros in the future? And maybe Planet Nine?

Eros, sure.

Planet nine, not until we know more about it.
Are you planing a CKAN integration?

Have been playing with this absolutely fantastic mod since I reloaded RSS and RO on my OS X  install (Thank you 64bit hack!). It's like having a live action Orrery - I love it.

Now, I concur regarding the polite request to add Eros - as our May 1975 launch window is rapidly approaching!  Our Eros Manned Flyby Mission will be failure if Eros does not show up in the tracking station ;-)

@pozine <<<---- Absolutely Amazing.  Thank you for this mod.  You have reinvigorated my KSP experience because of it. If I could find your "Donate" link, I would, ah... DONATE!

Please do more space engine textures! They are beautiful and the only reason they are really scorned is that they dont fit in with the cartoony look of existing worlds. But RSS breaks that graphical style anyway so its perfectly ok if not better.
